    {
      "instruction": "<p>While everything's cooking, combine your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>in a large bowl – this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>After 5 min, remove the meat-free chick'n tray from the oven and sprinkle over the<strong> grated cheese</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 5 min further or until the cheese has melted – this is your <strong>cheesy BBQ meat-free chick'n</strong></p>",
